You are planning the setup of an Android device before a UI test runs.

Several independent preconditions must all be established on the device.
They are applied one after another: each precondition is set up on the
device state the previous one left behind, and only the first one starts
from a freshly reset device. The device is left exactly where the LAST
precondition finishes, and that screen becomes the starting point for the
test — so the final precondition decides where the test begins.

Order them so that:
- Preconditions that only set up background or global state come FIRST.
  These include connectivity, signing in or choosing an account,
  granting permissions, app installation, and making files, messages, or
  other data available. They can be satisfied by navigating anywhere; the
  screen they happen to end on does not matter, because a later
  precondition will move the device to its final position.
- A precondition that pins a specific visible screen or on-screen
  location comes LAST (for example "the X screen is visible"). Establishing
  it last guarantees the device is actually left on that screen for the
  test.
- If two preconditions both pin a screen, the one matching where the
  test's first step starts goes last. When two preconditions are
  otherwise equivalent, keep their original relative order.

### Preconditions
